<<<code>>>: 
```java
public Iterator<Integer> getEvenNumbers(Iterator<Integer> iterator) {
    List<Integer> evenNumbers = new ArrayList<>();
    while(iterator.hasNext()) {
        int number = iterator.next();
        if(number % 2 == 0) {
            evenNumbers.add(number);
        }
    }
    return evenNumbers.iterator();
}
```
<<<explanation>>>: This function uses a while loop to iterate over the given iterator. It checks if the current number is even by using the modulus operator (%). If the number is even, it is added to the list of even numbers. Finally, the iterator for the list of even numbers is returned.
